ItemECommerce.longDescription:
The Whistler is a great option for paddlers wanting to move up from a recreational kayak, or start out with a seaworthy transitional design.

     Stable and very user friendly, the upswept bow makes the Whistler highly maneuverable while keeping you dry when waves kick up.

    This kayak features the Revolution Seating System (rotating axis controlled by a lever-lock system to adjust the angle of seat bottom) and the Dimension Adjustable Seat Back (a fully articulating and height/angle adjustable back rest). The Whistler is designed with thigh braces, a bow hatch/bulkhead and a stern hatch/bulkhead. The optional rudder is included on this kayak. 

These kayaks bridge the gap between recreational and touring kayaks -- the perfect step for paddlers looking to transition from a recreational kayak or seasoned paddlers looking for a day tripping kayak.
